ionDomain` after formatting. I need to check that the formatted access can be asserted and that the dynamic report verifies everything. It seems I need to extend the `PatternFormatter(\\\"%E\\\")` to handle source lines correctly. When dealing with class loading, I think `Class.forName(name, false, tccl)` is returning what I need. I should also consider whether our SecurityManager checks `RuntimePermission(\\\"getClassLoader\\\")` based on the class loader hierarchy. It might help to use a caching map in the formatter instance for efficiency!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining security manager settings**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the test setup and the fact that it doesn't specifically guard against issues related to setting the SecurityManager in JDK 24. There's an interesting point about a potential Unchecked Operation Exception (UOE) when trying to set the security manager. Since the current date is 2026, it’s possible we’re dealing with JDK 24 or newer versions. This raises questions about compatibility and what changes may have been implemented in the security framework since then.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_w3BlkbYB38DaflUke6wfBdxP|fc_0664f544a4c8a1fa0169effe16c8ec81a3ab9fd859b6650965", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"runtimeArgs|jvmArgs|buildArgs\" tests/src -g build.gradle | head -80"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 297, "output": 1795, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24108, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777335798783, "responseId": "resp_0664f544a4c8a1fa0169effdf7453081a38de26bc4c755d407"}}
